This paper deals with resource allocation in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The paper also uses game theory to formulate the problem, which suggests that it could be categorized under the subfield of game theory and decision making (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses power allocation and transmission rate optimization, which are topics that fall under the subfield of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes a novel algorithm for joint access point selection and power allocation, which could be categorized under the subfield of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses simulations and performance evaluation, which suggests that it could be categorized under the subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
